        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>You adopt the stance of clinging shadows. You can make shadow grasp @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Strike]{Strikes}. These deal [[/r 1d4 #negative]] negative damage; are in the brawling group; and have the agile, grapple, reach, and unarmed traits.</p>\n<p>While in clinging shadows stance, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Athletics checks to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Grapple]{Grapple}, and to the DC for creatures to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Escape]{Escape} from you.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.feat-effects.Stance: Clinging Shadows Stance]{Stance: Clinging Shadows Stance}</p>"
